OL,3,CPolice 'spying' report short on all
OL,4,Cassurances: Policing Board
OL,6,FThe report added that the "remainder
OL,7,Fof the applications did not seek to
OL,8,Fidentify a journalist's source and
OL,9,Ftheir profession may have been
OL,10,Fentirely unrelated to the request".
OL,12,FThe report also revealed that in the
OL,13,Fsame time period there were 500
OL,14,Fapplications for communications data
OL,15,Frelated to lawyers who were victims,
OL,16,Fsuspects or witnesses to crime.
OL,18,FThe figures were placed in the context
OL,19,Fthat the PSNI makes around 8,500
OL,20,Fcommunication data requests annually
OL,21,Ffor a range of criminal offences.
