OL,3,CPolice 'spying' report short on all
OL,4,Cassurances: Policing Board
OL,6,FIt was also contended that the main
OL,7,Fpower police use is for communications
OL,8,Fdata only, described as the "who,
OL,9,Fwhere, when and how" of communication,
OL,10,Fbut "not what was said, written or
OL,11,Fspoken".
OL,13,FThe report was published online on
OL,14,FThursday following a private meeting
OL,15,Fof the Policing Board in Belfast.
OL,17,FAhead of the meeting in Belfast on
OL,18,FThursday a protest, organised by the
OL,19,FNational Union of Journalists, called
OL,20,Ffor an inquiry into allegations of the
OL,21,FPSNI spying on journalists.
